            "description": "Implement Rust CLI NetSniff tool",
            "prompt": "Implement a complete Rust CLI tool called \"netsniff\" for sniffing Android app HTTP traffic. This is a new project at `/Users/a.vladislavov/personal/adb_tool/`.\n\n## Architecture\n\nThe tool acts as a WebSocket **server**. An Android plugin (OkHttp interceptor) connects to it as a WebSocket client, sending captured HTTP transactions as JSON. The CLI displays them in real-time with filtering and coloring.\n\n## File Structure to Create\n\n```\n/Users/a.vladislavov/personal/adb_tool/\n├── Cargo.toml          # workspace\n└── cli/\n    ├── Cargo.toml\n    └── src/\n        ├── main.rs\n        ├── server.rs\n        ├── protocol.rs\n        ├── display.rs\n        └── filter.rs\n```\n\n## Protocol\n\nAndroid plugin sends JSON messages. Two message types:\n\n**Hello** (sent on connection):\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"hello\",\n  \"clientId\": \"uuid\",\n  \"appPackage\": \"com.netsniff.sample\",\n  \"deviceModel\": \"Pixel 7\",\n  \"androidVersion\": \"14\"\n}\n```\n\n**Transaction** (one per HTTP request):\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"transaction\",\n  \"id\": \"uuid\",\n  \"timestamp\": 1234567890000,\n  \"method\": \"GET\",\n  \"url\": \"https://swapi.dev/api/people/1/\",\n  \"requestHeaders\": {\"Authorization\": \"Bearer ...\"},\n  \"requestBody\": null,\n  \"requestSizeBytes\": 0,\n  \"responseCode\": 200,\n  \"responseMessage\": \"OK\",\n  \"responseHeaders\": {\"Content-Type\": \"application/json; charset=utf-8\"},\n  \"responseBody\": \"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Luke Skywalker\\\"...}\",\n  \"responseSizeBytes\": 1024,\n  \"durationMs\": 342,\n  \"appId\": \"com.netsniff.sample\",\n  \"error\": null\n}\n```\n\nIf request failed (network error):\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"transaction\",\n  \"id\": \"uuid\",\n  \"timestamp\": 1234567890000,\n  \"method\": \"GET\",\n  \"url\": \"https://swapi.dev/api/people/1/\",\n  \"requestHeaders\": {},\n  \"requestBody\": null,\n  \"requestSizeBytes\": 0,\n  \"responseCode\": null,\n  \"responseMessage\": null,\n